dReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=118.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   How can mages powerlevel people??</span><hr size=1> I have a level 44 mage and my friend is a level 24 wizard.  I want to powerlevel him closer to my level so we can kill things together but I have no idea where to do the powerleveling.  If anyone has any experience powerleveling other people with a mage please respond with where you did it!  thanks! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=waldenawildfyre>Waldena Wildfyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#333333>(12/5/00 12:37:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=118.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How can mages powerlevel people??</span><hr size=1> Because mages cant FD to clear argo and give someone else full xp, they cant heal or buff someone, or they cant cast a dot, powerleveling with a mage wouldnt be as good as with a cleric/chanter, monk, druid, necro, shaman, druid or SK (cleric/chanter is best combo for melee class because it allows the person to do all the fighting to keep their skills up).  For a mage to pl a wizard i would think the magician should cast the highest version of malise they have, then have wiz or earth pet root (if you do earth pet make sure to back off after root is on) then have wiz blast it down to lil less then 1/2 health then have mage send in pet to finish job.  Will level a wiz faster because they wouldnt have to group and they wont have to use much mana per fihgt and will be safe if root breaks. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uknackerjacker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KnackerJacker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(12/5/00 6:49:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=118.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re</span><hr size=1> I have powerleveled people before by summoning a pet and having it attack the mob then when the mob is almost dead I tell the pet to get lost... This works pretty well but I have no idea what mobs I should be powerleveling a level 24 on... Thanks for the reply!  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> magician</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(12/6/00 2:10:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=118.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   powerleveling</span><hr size=1> I have a level 54 mage and I can tell you two ways to powerlevel.  First cast the damage shield on the fighter.  As long as the person hits the npc for one point then they will get the ex.  If the person sits back and inflicts no damage while relying on the ds then they get no ex.  For instance person swings at npc and misses.  Npc hits ds and dies (really low level), no ex for the person.  Here is a second way to power level someone.  I was a level 51 mage at the time.  I took a level 22 druid into Kedges keep.  I pull one lancer snd in the pet.  Do not ds the pet.  Cast a ds on the druid.  Druid spells do no affect the lancers,they are too high.  Druid moves in and hits the lancer once only.  Then steps back.  The lancer will hit the pc by the way.  So don't take a newbie in to do this.  The person must have some hitpoints.  When the lancer is 80 to 90 percent dead you zone.  Pet dies.  Lancer aggroes on pc.  Since pc has a 25 ds up lancer kills himself against the ds.  About three kills for a bubble of ex to this druid.  Perhaps just killing the pet would allow the druid the ex. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uommundanrii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ommundan Rii</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://home.cfl.rr.com/exarch/x.bmp BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master of The Hunt</span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#333333>(1/1/01 9:50:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=118.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.cfl.rr.com/exarch/SUMMON.BMP WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How can mages powerlevel people??</span><hr size=1> We can't heal, but we can bandage with the best of them <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Or we shold be able to anyway since they are free to us <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Seriously, I've powerleveled a person barely into 7th lvl up to half way through 9th in less than an hour. Through bandaging as he fought, and damage shields and finishing nukes.<br>
<br>
Of course at 24th bandaging is not a viable option since our skill caps it so there is no way we can keep up with what creatures can dish out.<br>
<br>
I do like the idea of working near a zone and getting a creature very low and then zoning to give them full exp. Great idea.<br>
<br>
I can tell you for sure that even if the pet dies, if you and the pet did more than half, you get the exp even if the pet dies.<br>
<br>
I have heard of another tactic that supposedly works. Similar to the zoning trick, you attack something like normal (something the person you're powerleveling can finish off) then when the creature is almost dead, you cast invisibility on yourself, killing the pet. Then the other person has to take over. Something about you can't gain exp from stuff while invis? I havenot tried this tactic in a while, but I may when I eventualy get back. If anyone can get a chance to try this out, let me know if it works. Might save some zoning time, or allow the tactic to be used in the middle of a zone <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
But really, in all honesty, befriend a druid <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  They are the undesputed masters of powerleveling <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Take care and good hunting!<br>
