Magi, Rodcet Nife</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unaginatakuroshio.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Naginata Kuroshio</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.rose-hulman.edu/~acuffnd/Reference/icon1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master of The Elements</span><br>  Posts: 88<br> <font color=#333333>(1/3/01 2:13:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=118.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How can mages powerlevel people??</span><hr size=1> Mages are the best mid-late powerlevelers in the game.  at 53, a level 36 person (my roommate, the ranger) will still get exp with you.  Go someplace where you can kill things really quickly (seafuries), where things give alot of exp (seafuries), and are red to the person you're powerleveling (seafuries).  I tried this at (big shocker) seafuries, and it worked well... an hour of killing stuff that's green to you and red to them will really bump that exp bar along for them <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><table width="100%" border="0">
