    <td width="314" align="right"><img src="http://www.rose-hulman.edu/~acuffnd/Reference/brewsig.gif" align="center"></td>
  </tr>
</table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=balthemal>Balthemal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#333333>(5/24/01 6:38:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=118.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How can mages powerlevel people??</span><hr size=1> I'm sorry about being so pessimistic here, but I have to point this out: If you want to powerlevel someone, the mage is NOT the class to do it on. Yes, we can do it. Yes, we can do it better than some classes. But if you really want to powerlevel someone, be a cleric/druid/enchanter. Major powerleveling involves something like this: Warrior is buffed by druid (level 45, let's say) Warrior (level 10, let's say) goes out and pulls about 10 BNRM's (Big Nasty Red Mobs). When warrior gets back, druid casts Shield of Spikes on him (think that's the right one. I'm talking about the one that does about 15 damage per hit). Warrior attacks, but most damage is done through Shield of Spikes. Warrior still gets the exp. Druid heals when nessicary. I tried this out with two friends. One was a 40 druid, the other was 46 at this time. I was a level 11 CLERIC. I had bronze armor, and only about 200hp unbuffed. Heh, I was in no way a melee type, but nevertheless I went from 11 to 15 in about half an hour. So, powerleveling could be even faster IF you had two friends, a mage and a cleric. Mage would do DS and cleric covers heals/buffs. Most people can't find TWO people to Powerlevel them, so druids would be the best overall powerlevelers.<br>
<br>
Hmm....Sorry for any cases of me not making sense. I'm thinking faster than I'm typing, which is not an easy thing to do at 3:00 AM... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umezlothemage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mezlo the Mage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#333333>(5/24/01 2:58:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=118.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How can mages powerlevel people??</span><hr size=1> I had a little luck powerleveling a 48 wizard at the bloodgills.  I would DS the pet and sic it.  The wizard would then KS the pet.  The pet was the meat shield and rooter for the wizard.  I would think you could do this at other levels by carefully picking your pet and damage shield.<br>
<br>
 <p>Mezlo, Mage of 51 Seasons, Drinal</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umezlothemage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mezlo the Mage</A> at: 5/24/01 12:42:14 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uevieofvazaelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evie of Vazaelle</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://webpages.mr.net/exin/eq/psypoke037.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 87<br> <font color=#333333>(5/24/01 8:13:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=118.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How can mages powerlevel people??</span><hr size=1> I've always heard that if you summon a pet, sic it on a mob, don't nuke at all, get it to where it's running, reclaim the pet, and have the person being PLed finish it off and they will get the exp.  Still, it doesn't compare to the druid powerleveling where you can grab 5-6 mobs, whack each of 'em once or twice, and let the DS finish them off.  I went from 1-20 with a druid powerleveling me for 8 hours.  Best place to powerlevel is kurns tower from 5-15.  Any places with undead who don't run is awesome.<br>
<br>
 <p>[54 Modrodulist] Evie (Useless) <<a
href="http://www.promethianorder.com">Promethian Order</a>>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubalanzsonofanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#333333>(5/24/01 11:38:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=118.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Space Cadet Stimpy Reporting for Duty!</span><hr size=1> I have done quite a bit of powerlevelling recently, both one on one, and in groups.  Once I understand an area well, and can solo there, I invite a blue ranger <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (they make the best bait...I mean pullers)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to join me at my camp, and give them a shopping list of the toughest things I can solo.  Then they fetch them to the loving arms of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Gobaner</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and the two of them finish off the enemy.  These pulls are usually pretty red to them, and as long as they can manage the aggro, it works like an assembly line.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Both</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> of us wind up getting pretty good experience under those circumstances.  Not only do Rangers <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> not</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> require any malachites to summon, but they can heal and buff as well.<br>
<br>
My other method involved group supervision.  I summon an <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> air</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> pet, one that is no more than yellow to the group, damage shield the tanks, and let them pull like mad.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Vbtik</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->'s stuns soften the enemy without stealing the kill, and damage shields are <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> awesome</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  And of course <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Malosi</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and such help the casters.<br>
<br>
I am not sure how I would power level a wizard though, and my inability to heal can be tragic <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (if they are dying, my only response is to open up a can of Whoopass, but it may be too late by then)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
I agree we are not the ideal powerlevels, but I often find a blue partner makes for a very pleasant and fruitful evening.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Razamatazz Pizzazz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Ancient Fraternity, Xev</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/urivern123.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RIVERN123</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#333333>(5/25/01 3:57:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=118.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How can mages powerlevel people??</span><hr size=1> I have done a fair bit of PL before. Mainly fighter class.<br>
Apart from doing fireshield, several things I observe, <br>
<br>
1. Always summon bandage for the fighter. Their bandage skill will become better than ours.<br>
<br>
2. Split the mob by pulling yourself. <br>
<br>
3. AC/HP play a big factor in PL. This is to minimise the amount of damage taken in a fight.<br>
<br>
Lastly but most important of all<br>
<br>
4. Bind them close by and let them die (!). This is the most effective way of heal. The xp you lose will be insignificant since you are PL him anyway.<br>
<br>
Also I notice for the grouping method, myself 52 and friend 36. My friend only get xp on a white con or higher. Not sure whether this is 100 % true or not.<br>
<br>
